				<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://www.npost.com/blog/2010/11/22/what-it-really-means-to-be-a-startup-cto/" title="What it really means to be a startup CTO" rel="bookmark">What it really means to be a startup CTO</a></h2>
		
		<div class="post-info"><span class="date time published" title="2010-11-22T08:31:27+0000">November 22, 2010</span>  By <span class="author vcard"><a href="http://www.npost.com/blog/author/npostadmin/" title="Posts by Nathan Kaiser" rel="nofollow">Nathan Kaiser</a></span> <span class="post-comments"><a href="http://www.npost.com/blog/2010/11/22/what-it-really-means-to-be-a-startup-cto/#comments" rel="nofollow">Leave a Comment</a></span> </div>		<div class="entry-content">
			<a href="http://www.npost.com/blog/2010/11/22/what-it-really-means-to-be-a-startup-cto/" title="What it really means to be a startup CTO"></a><p><strong>See original post at <a href="\\\\\\\">Dan Shapiro</a>:</strong></p>
<div><a href="http://twitter.com/share?url=http%3A%2F%2Fbit.ly%2FaOrO7q&amp;via=danshapiro&amp;text=What+it+really+means+to+be+a+startup+CTO&amp;lang=en&amp;count=horizontal&amp;counturl=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.danshapiro.com%2Fblog%2F2010%2F11%2Fwhat-it-really-means-to-be-a-startup-cto%2F">Tweet</a></div>
